In the process of writing this column, one constituted a WhatsApp group discussion of friends and acquaintances to solicit views on at least five highlights of 2019 and another five mustdos for our country over the next year. Only a handful offered less than five, most diligently provided the minimum number while others catalogued more. Although none of them put it in these words, they would nonetheless concur with a characterisation that 2019 was, certainly for our country, thoroughly Dickensian. To place the claim in context, here is a famous and evocative opening passage from A Tale Of Two Cities,...